    "body": "### Problem\n\nHi there, I use ohmyzsh to lazily start node/npm https://github.com/ohmyzsh/ohmyzsh/tree/master/plugins/nvm (`zstyle ':omz:plugins:nvm' lazy yes`)\nHowever I get the following error when LSPs try to parse any file relying on node:\n\n```\n[ERROR][2024-12-06 22:28:52] .../vim/lsp/rpc.lua:770\t\n  \"rpc\"\t\"/Users/xxxxxxx/.local/share/nvim/mason/bin/vtsls\"\t\n  \"stderr\"\t\"env: node: No such file or directory\\n\"\n```\n\nNeovim version\n\n```\nNVIM v0.10.2\nBuild type: Release\nLuaJIT 2.1.1732813678\n\n   system vimrc file: \"$VIM/sysinit.vim\"\n  fall-back for $VIM: \"/opt/homebrew/Cellar/neovim/0.10.2_1/share/nvim\"\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\n# assuming you have an LSP that is able to parse js code (vtsls)\nnvim any-file.js\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNeovim should wait until node is lazily linked and the LSPs should work as expected.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.10.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.1.1 (24B91)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\niTerm 3.5.10\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew",
